hr.caellian.flow.data

Interface PropertyManager

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Flux<S>

    public interface PropertyManager
    Property Manager is an interface marking a class capable of containing Properties in a form of a map.
    Since:
    1.0.0

      • setValue

        default <T> T setValue(java.lang.String id,
                       T newValue)
        This method will modify already registered property or add it to the map if it isn't currently contained within the map.
        Type Parameters:
        T - property type.
        Parameters:
        id - id of a property to set value to.
        newValue - value to set for given property id.
        Returns:
